The story holds a very linear plot, with constant characters and a good use of flashbacks. There were a few moments where I felt it could have been better, especially towards the ending, but that's about it. The pregnancy was unrealistic but expected, and a welcomed plot element at the end of the doujin.

The art was good, and not overly exaggerated in the usual ways. Perhaps the distended belly of the now pregnant main character could have used a touch up in a few of the more artistic scenes, but overall there were little to no flaws.

I feel as if we could use an extra page putting everything a bit more into perspective, give us a bit more depth into the characters, but that's all really.

Final rating? 8/10, I would reccomend this to people I know well enough.
